  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Mark 8:34-38",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Mark 8:34-38",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "When he had called the people unto him ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— To hear a truth of the last importance, and one that equally concerned them all; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whosoever will come after ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "me — And be a disciple of mine, entitled to all the privileges and blessings which belong to my disciples in this world and the next; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "let him deny himself ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— His own will, in all things, great and small, however pleasing, and that continually; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and take up his cross ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Embrace the will of God, however painful, daily, hourly, continually. Thus only can he ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "follow me ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in holiness to glory. See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 16:24-26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Whosoever shall be ashamed of me ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Poor, despised, and a man of sorrows though I am; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and of my words ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, of avowing by word and action whatever I have said, particularly this my precept of self-denial, and taking up the daily cross: and whosoever is not heartily willing to sustain the scoffs of a wicked world, to which the profession and practice of my religion may expose him; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of him also shall the Son of man be ashamed,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " &c. — He shall be ashamed to acknowledge one for his disciple who has acted in a manner so unlike his Master, and so unworthy of his religion. See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:32-33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
