  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 34.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "He called unto him the multitude with his disciples",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This shows that there was an interval between what had just taken place and what is now recorded. Our Lord now, without any further special reference to St. Peter, delivers a lesson of universal application; although, no doubt, he had Peter in his mind",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": ". If any man would",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἴ τις θέλει",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This self-denial ought to extend to everything, even to life itself, which we ought to be willing to resign, if need be, for the sake of Christ. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Take up his cross.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It is as though he said, \"Let him take up his cross, as I have borne my cross, that I might be the standard-bearer and Leader of all cross",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "-",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
